Kevin McAleenan says in the interview airing Sunday that he regrets the way the policy was carried out.
President Trump named McAleenan as acting head of the department following the resignation of Kirstjen Nielsen.
In the 60 Minutes report, Alfonsi shows border patrol stations overwhelmed with families the secretary says DHS is trying to house.
"We have learned that DHS actually did start building two tent cities along the border in Texas," Alfonsi said.
The full 60 Minutes report airs Sunday, April 28 at 7 p.m. ET/PT on CBS.